values:
it's times like this when
losing touch
time
reality
meaning
understanding
starts to make sense.
or not.
flashing
detached, from
everything
i can and will
distance myself from you
or her
or them
me.
spiral falling face gun. repeat.
aside from loneliness
it's the one cycle on repeat.
i'm falling.
as if i still even have this damn journal... does anyone still post on here?

repetitive beats
answers to nothing
figuring things out
i am strong
i can cope
work so hard
to watch me fall
red wheels
pounding foot steps
hustling along
pushing feelings further
back
then ever before
forgetting you
losing touch
kind of like faith
in life
settling down
with my self
again.
too embarrassed
go away.

one beat
teeth still chattering
make it stop
i clarified i wanted 
honesty
even if i can't hear it
i could see it
my gut is weighed down
with it
who is telling the truth
does it really matter
anymore
i just know that my
beating (hurt) heart
is still in your hand
ripped out
no life pumping to it
and i'm still breathing
because i've remembered to.
i feel with my heart 
and i'm relearning how
to not think
with my heart.

there is clarity in
the 
absence of breath.
fortunate or
unfortunate
i am still breathing
another countdown
to nothing
is underway
am i going to stick around
no one can answer this 
no part of me has this
answer
no part of me is ready for the
answer

sudden falls
left behind
sandwiched
between water
and love
and hate
there's this constant exercise
this back and forth motion
why tell me your dreams
really why tell me
anything
last to know
all i have to hold onto
is lies
all i want to hold onto is
you.

pictures 
scenes
shots
green leaves
melting away
i remember tomorrow
like it was yesterday
my eyes keep flickering
i've worked in these fields
before
i leave
the 
the 
needed
less 
than
falling down again.

lines restored
six tiny cuts
what am i doing here
forgot to hide
how to
words pour out
silent
if outside was 
812 SE 30th
if downstairs still
loved me
woosh
problem problem
present.
still.
inside inside

sometimes i feel like i
could explode
or implode
curl up inside of me
safe place
red cards
don't get your hopes up
you aren't a significant part
you are the small fraction
lines down
no one minds
somewhere i mind
but mostly i just sit
eyes half open
replaying words
reliving actions

still waiting to find
my inspiration
in me.

on my back
restraint
frozen
the phone rings
i know i won't answer it
maybe i should just go to sleep
she talks a lot about not 
being perfect

detaching a rhythm of life
souls connecting
bad motives
tightening my fist
i am not me
reflecting ideas
counting down to the collapse
my thoughts won't ever push out
of this room
trapped in time
15 again
still no friends
i feel asexual
no meaning
too many fucking people have been raped
detaching life from rhythm

pains behind me
my skin crawls
we keep moving  forward 
only to  discuss taking
two steps back
i stop wondering why everything
seems so familiar
my body just might collapse.
everything would still be just 
out of reach
which is why we may never touch
touching myself
doesn't mean nearly as much
now that i've touched you
and breathed in 
your same breath
14 hours 
a countdown to nothing.

bed time
my eye to my ear
eyebrows don't count
protruding inward
scratching my eyes
perfectly cut lawns
dysfunctional inside
you don't need to appear
so okay
phone bills can be waived
change of scenery
i felt my heart slow and
a calm over my body
i was able to breathe
in slowly
and out slowly
i truly felt secure today
with her in my life
the clocks started.

i keep seeing snow flakes falling
from this white/gray cloudy sky 
they're falling down on my face
turning to tears
freezing me to death.
here's some photos from my trip to canada, and here's me and jess...
at the party.... hahaha lian coming in from behind on phylo

my little peechka came to visit me (and her family) this past weekend. i don't think i've smiled this much since like i don't know when... everyone at work today and over the weekend kept telling me how good i looked, they kept saying i looked so happy. today my coworker said "you're so happy and being so funny today" whatever bitch i'm always funny... haha just kidding so ya it feels good to feel happy again, i hope this keeps up. I've decided that for the month of august i will try and go to NYC to see lian and kate and tammy. and of course all the other folks i know there. I've been making tiara's other half of her birthday gift today. lian i decided to make her the riot grrl mix tape, it's so amazing already i feel like i may need to make two tapes, cus there's so much stuff i wanna put on them... lian and i also found these videos of old bikini kill shows while we were at the phobia show last weekend... one is from two shows in DC in 92 and the other is from a show in MA in 95... i gave my coworker the tapes and she is going to dub them for me. i should be getting my other bike and some wheels i won on ebay this week so that's exciting, and i think i may sell one of the bikes i won on ebay cus i don't know when i'll get the time to build it up. i think more people should come visit me soon, please?
i need sleep. and i've also decided i need to make out with someone, it's been too long.

don't be jealous. YES! i'm so fucking excited... this weekend is going to rule. we can be gay at long beach pride and ride bikes around and we can go visit friends that i haven't even seen since i've been back and most of all we can laugh together and at each other, and make more funny memories together... i don't know if we could top taping the lights to the wall and ceiling with scotch tape while on k, or our many renditions of sleater-kinney song, but i know we'll try.
in other news, vonzelle got voted off american idol... that's right american idol, my parents have me watching this shit... haha but anyway... 
so i've been having bad pains again, like the pains i used to get when i found out i had an ovarian cyst. i haven't been to the doctor for that shit in like 3 or 4 years... so i was a good girl and i printed out a list of gynecologists in my area... now how the hell am i suppose to know from a name if they are going to be horrible or not here are some names...
Kim, Jaime E
Mahato, Prem P
Marolia, Bharat B
Accetta, August D
Dubyak, Johanna M
Han, William I
Illeck, Jeffrey S
Feldman, Bernard M
Korber, Patricia K
Lee, Christina J

that's like just a few, now which one would you choose. I know i don't want a guy cus the last one i had was a guy and he was a fucking dick... i was in so much pain wheni saw him and he did his little exam with his fucking huge man hands and then when he removed his hand and i was STILL crying, he asked me WHY i was crying, since he had already taken his hand out... like that was the sole reason for me crying... fucking prick, i wonder why i haven't been back to the gyno since.  
eh... ok i'm super tired i need to sleep... i have a big day tomorrow, yeah!

so i've been sick for ohhhh 2 weeks now, the doctor says i have a "bad" sinus infection, no shit sherlock. but whatever i got antibiotics, and some allergy medicine... i'm all drugged up and ready to go. i went on this really long bike ride yesterday from huntington beach to long beach, and had lunch with this girl that works at the peet's there, then on the ride home i thought i was going to die, let's just say i hadn't planned on the wind factor. and my feet kept going numb on me, like i had no circulation in my feet or something. i finally went online today to my kryptonite lock replaced, that only took me like a year.
ok so i am SO FUCKING EXCITED lian is coming here this thursday, and for the first time in like 3 months i'm soooo happy, it'll be nice having someone that i love to pieces to hang out with... 
in other friend news... the one in pdx is kinda pissing me off, she has this too good for you attitude, so i've decided to not talk to her for a couple days, see if that helps. 
i was thinking that i need some like bolt of lightening to strike me so i stop spending my money on bikes, i wanna move FAR away. and the sooner i pay this shit off the sooner i can go play with lian in NY and the sooner i can move back to my lovely pdx...

I will try to make this quick and not so fucking depressing... 

i had to work this morning at 4:45am bleh, but my coworker accidently came in at the same time so she said she would stay and i got to go home and go back to sleep... yeah! i needed it cus i'm STILL trying to shake this sick/flu/cold thing that i've had for a week now. so anyway i slept and then went to work at the gypsy den where i worked all of about 4 hours and then left to go home. 
(insert circus music) 
let me back track to a week ago... i came out to my car at this parking structure and i had a warning note on my car stating that "i am parked in an oversized vehicle area" for those of you who know what i drive, you would think... well yes danielle HAS an oversized truck... not that it's huge but it's definitely not a fucking geo metro or something, so anyway i talk to the lady and she says she doesn't know what to say cus she didn't give me the warning... 
now today, so i decide today that ok, i will park where they want me to park... so i park and while i'm leaving i notice they have these cones in the middle of this already exceptionally SMALL turn, and for a moment i consider running them over, because well it just sounds fun, but i don't and so i make the first turn and then i go to make the second sharp turn, and BOOM! i apparently hit a curb with my tire. i don't really think much of it because it was pretty unavoidable unless i had run down the cones... so i pull up to leave and then the guy tells me you know your tire just exploded.... 
(insert laughter) 
why laughter, well why not, there's no use getting upset over this shit anymore i mean oh well right? so i'm sitting there thinking well at least i have a spare tire. and then i realize shit when my keys got lost at the ludacris concert like a year ago my spare key tire was on there so now i can't really remove my spare tire it's just stuck up underneath my car...  and then i come to the other conclusion that i don't have AAA. so i decide i will take the tire off and go to the tire store with the tire and make them just change it and i'll put it back on when i get back to the tire... like 45 minutes goes by and i finish all that... (that's right this bitch can change a tire like faster then lightening) 
so then i leave the parking structure and notice this weird smell thing... (side note) occasionally my truck has been leaking coolant lately... so now my car is leaking massive amounts of coolant... so i had to take my truck in to get the water pump fixed... there goes another $275... have i mentioned i HATE having a car.. i just want a little vespa with a side car, that lian can ride in. and i wanna like figure out some way to put a bike rack on it... that's all i want... some day it will happen... so ya that was my day... don't be jealous.

question: if you wanted nothing to do with someone ever again, then why would you go around stealing all of their friends of 6+ years? i'm sick of all the bullshit here. i've decided that i do not exist in LA anymore. from here on out i live in portland or san francisco, or new york. anywhere but here. i have absolutely nothing here anymore. unless you count my bikes. 
lian did i tell you that christina and rod are getting married on july 2nd? and vanya and eric are moving back to pdx in august, things might be falling back into place up there i'm excited.

day two of being a sick mofo! i seriously can't deal with being at peet's anymore, i've officially started looking for new jobs, which is sooo annoying to me meh! but hey why stay somewhere that doesn't appreciate you at all, i say let the store go down and when they go down i hope it goes down hard.... i'm going to run off for a shower and then to bed cus i work 8-10am and then 12:30-9pm yes all at fantastic peets.... xo

if i don't have to ever train another person again, it'll be too soon. at the gypsy den i trained a girl today who asked me what and why i was doing anything and everything... i swear if i leaned a little too much to the left she'd ask so why'd you do that... normally i think questions are good when i'm training someone but today it was thoroughly annoying. and then tonight at peets this fucking kid just left, he wasn't even done being trained because "he had a party to go to" all i have to say to that is fucking moron. 
i finally tried to track down my hypnotherapist last night since when i stopped by his office a week or so ago, he was no longer there... and last night i discovered he's now living in florida, which fucking sucks cus he's probably the only person who's ever helped me get myself better. but i e-mailed him and and asked if he could recommend be to someone else, or if he ever does seminars out here still. so he e-mailed me back and gave me his office number and cell phone number, so i will try calling him tomorrow. 
lian i'm so fucking excited yr coming out here soon... k i just had to say that... and i'm excited to go to nyc... i wanna hang out and make out... haha aww yeah!

so i can't stop buying bikes on ebay this is the latest one... let me know what you think and it came with these cranks.. so jordan finally called me tonight. i think i got more frustrated then anything. i hate it when you think yr talking with someone and maybe kinda connecting and then they drop off the face of the earth for weeks. but eh, i'm weird what can i say, oh yes and according to some "i need help" neat. so anyway when i actually went to call her back from the number she called me from it was some guys cell phone... so whatever... i'm getting more and more closed off to people these days. i really need to get my shit together soon.

sunday: went out for drinks with my coworker in orange county, was asked by some moron if i would have sex with him (DO I LOOK LIKE I WANNA HAVE SEX WITH SOME FUCKING MORON?) i looked at him laughed and said hell no, then when he asked why i told him i was fucking gay... don't i look like i swing for the ladies? 
monday: got bitched out by angela, and now angela and rosy have become best friends and rosy won't return any of my calls or talk to me anymore, hence i am through with rosy we are no longer friends. 6+ years of friendship has come to an end, why? i still don't know what i did. also later this evening while getting yelled at by angela, jordan calls me to tell me she got evicted and lost her job, so we were emo on the phone together. i talked to my mom about everything going on and that was good but just made me sad and made me wonder if rosy made up all the shit about the squab kids. then my cell phone got thrown down on the ground and the screen broke so now i can't see who's calling me, it sucks.
tuesday: i worked and felt like shit because of the loss of my best friend. waited at the DMV for two hours convincing the lady to allow me to register my car in two states so i don't have to pay all over again in oregon, she finally let me. then about 15 minutes after leaving the DMV my dad called me to tell me that in one week, next wednesday, we have to testify in court against the people who broke into my house. now let me just say that this upsets me, i did not want to have to see these people. i just started being able to sleep again with the help of sleeping medicine because of the break in. 
today: i received a phone call from allison. she called to tell me that her old housemate chris, trish's boyfriend died this past weekend. apparently he was in mexico working on an organic farm there of some sort and he had gone swimming and he drowned, they have yet to find his body. allison is really sad which makes me really sad and i can't even imagine what trish and tara are going through. i think i may drive to sf this weekend to see allison i think i need to get out of here for a little bit.

i wanna cry cus things just won't go right... ok i am crying cus things just won't go right. i've been working here in ca since like december. i just got a letter in the mail the other day saying i HAVE to register my car here blah blah blah... yet i've payed oregon through next like march... this is an additional 100 200 dollars i will have to spend... i want something to work for me and i fucking want a friend here to cry to. and i really wanna go buy drugs and say fuck so many things right now. i also hit my damn chin tonight on the desk at work getting into the safe, so it feels like it's bruised... i was going to go see anthony on sunday down in san diego, but now i may just stay in bed and sleep for two days... i haven't felt like i was falling so much since the year before i moved to portland. now i know how i ended up at the beach with the cops. and now i know why drugs were my vice before... i just want to escape.

so i have decided after a much draining last couple of weeks, that something has to change.  Something that will not only make me feel better but make me nicer to people around me, and not so fucking irritable. So i've decided to cut sugar out of my diet again, i'm going to shoot for a month and go from there. So wish me luck.  
things have been weird in my life as usual lately.  i've been talking a lot to an ex, and we're planning a trip together, i just don't want to feel like i'm being enclosed like i did the last time with her. i don't really know what i want from her right now, i know i want for me to be happy again and that's all i'm really trying to focus on right now. I've also been talking with this other girl i have this crush on.  I've had a crush on her for a few months now, catch is she lives in portland and i don't think it would be smart for me to act on any feelings that i'm having right now mainly because i don't know where they are coming from. maybe loneliness, boredom, sadness, or maybe i really like her who the fuck knows anymore, i know i don't which is why i don't think i should react to it. 
i got my new/old drum set today. it's an old gretsch drum set, i am currently researching what year and it's value i have a few of the model/serial numbers so if any one has any websites that would have any info on this i would love you sooo much. 
I'm finding this need to do something creative lately. i'm kinda kicking myself in the ass for thinking rosy would actually follow through with something and actually make time to play music with me. it's too fucking bad i'm so fucking insecure musically, it really prevents me from doing anything creative.  and i still wish barb wouldn't have been such an idiot, cus we actually sounded really good together. oh well though good riddance to her.
I got all my paper work today and filled it out so i can get a new passport. i'm starting to get nervous about this trip, it's like 5 months away, i hope i pay off the car in time... 
i'm so damn tired from no sugar i thin ki'm going to sleep like a baby tonight...
here's another photo for you or my hurrrr.... you still can't see it well though..

so i know it's like the first or second week of spring, but i can feel summer coming like it's tomorrow, everyone has their plans all set for where they are going to be and what they're going to be doing. And i have discovered that summer just might be the hardest time of year for me, (damn you K) just joking it's not your fault that i had the raddest summer ever when you were in town. i just miss the family i had two years ago. i miss the pool parties with my peechka, and the pool parties where i was getting dunked in a kitty pool. i fucking just miss having friends near me. i don't know how to do any link shit on here but here's one photo from last summer....

first of all YEAH! i got to garden today, i planted all sorts of vegetables and herbs in my back yard today, and I also sort of bought a drumset. I say sort of because i haven't officially paid for it yet, but it's a gretsch drumset from the late 80's.  A customer of mine from peet's is selling it to me, it used to be her husbands, and she is moving back to japan so she doesn't want to take it there obviously. i think i may go cut and dye my hair today also it's getting way too fucking long. maybe i'll take photo's of it when i'm done... but don't get your hopes up.
these made me miss pdx even more.

i absolutely HATE libby. i got kicked out of her house because i was sick.  even though i had a fever and could hardly breathe! thank god for bobby and amber's house they've rescued me twice now since i've been back to portland for visits. and caitlin since i was not very coherent when i was at your house THANK YOU SO MUCH for letting me crash at your house for the night. i guess i will sum up my trip like this...
i hate libby
i kinda hate angela
i miss portland
i miss all my friends in portland
i miss the rain
i miss the beautiful trees and plants and flowers 
i miss the old duplex, not the new one
i was happy to get to hang out with elodie, she took care of my sick ass
i hate so cal
the end.

um i don't know if my last entry went through..... so i'll write this shitty stuff again.... i'm sad my coworker from the gypsy den accidently overdoesed this past weekend while he was on vacation in seattle.  i keep thinking that this is a bad dream or something. he was so sweet and had such a big heart. everything just feels unreal right now.

i love how full of emotion everyone is on here. maybe something aside from this confused lonely feeling will rub off on me soon, then again i'm ok with being lonely, it's being smothered that's making me feel really lonely. i could use a buffy analogy here you know to humor myself, but i will refrain. i work in 10 hours and i couldn't sleep right now to save my life. 
caitlin what do you know about rolfing... this customer at my work is a rolfing practitioner, and i know it's named after a dr. but it reminds me of vomiting every time i say rolfing, anyway thumbs up or down.  i need to do something i'm having a hard time walking again without pain. any advice?

i think i need to go see my hypnotherapist again it's been a few years, but i feel like i'm losing control of things again.lots and lots of bad thoughts. for the first time ever in my life i felt like i was actually getting old.  i'll be 26 in a few weeks and it's just so close to 30 it's scarey. and i thin ki'll go quit my other job today at the gypsy den, i need a day or two off this working everyday thing is killing me.

or maybe it's orange county in general, or maybe california, it's killing my fucking soul. elodie was just here visiting, maybe she shouldn't have seen me here like this.  a huge piece of me is missing and she noticed right away.  i feel like i have no life in me. now i know why i do drugs when i'm here, it makes time fly. but i made a deal so now i can't do them, so now the days are just trickling by second by second. i just have to keep focused on working and paying off my car, i'm shooting for the summer time... if anyone in southern cali, has any ideas of making extra money let me know, i wanna make it out of here this time with my sanity. and just for the record i miss you portland. and i miss my friends, and i'm sorry i haven't spoke to anyone, but i still hurt too much to let any of you hear my voice. soon though.

so yes today i start back at peet's but not in the soggy northwest, in SUNNY SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA! ask me how not excited i am... and i'll tell you i'd rather still be living in my house with no heat getting sick every other week... but hey how long could i keep doing that??  so it seems really scattered when i actually get to talk to anyone, i don't really feel ready to see anyone from here so i have been staying home and not answering the phone.. i haven't even seen rosy, i mean she lives almost two hours away from me anyway... being home isn't just weird for the obvious fact that i haven't lived here in almost 4 years, but because my parents have remodeled so much that everything is different.... there's tile now where there was once carpet, and it's making me feel two inches taller, it's making me feel older, like i have outgrown this house and this town.  i have decided to leave everything in my room the way my mom has it, one because she'll freak out if i touch anything and two, because it'll remind me that i need to get back to where i am suppose to be, with elodie up in the rainy northwest, where i won't get killed when i try to ride my bike 3 blocks to the store, where the checker at the grocery store and the girl bagging groceries won't think i'm completely crazy for using my own back to carry my groceries home... and then insisting on me taking a plastic bag to put my bread in, even though it is already in a plastic bag. i even explained that to them and they just laughed... so considering how fucking bored i have been here i made an astrology chart last night for myself... maybe i'll post it, i think some of the stuff is a crock of shit but there is some truth to some of it... what do you all think? i don't know how to make a link for you to click on so it doesn't all post on here so here it is....

Your Sun Sign is in Capricorn

Capricorn
December 22 - January 19 
Capricorn, the tenth Sign of the Zodiac, is all about hard work. Those born under this Sign are more than happy to put in a full day at the office, realizing that it will likely take a lot of those days to get to the top. That's no problem, since Capricorns are both ambitious and determined: they will get there. Life is one big project for these folks, and they adapt to this by adopting a businesslike approach to most everything they do. Capricorns are practical as well, taking things one step at a time and being as realistic and pragmatic as possible. The Capricorn-born are extremely dedicated to their goals, almost to the point of stubbornness. Boy, those victories sure smell sweet, though, and that thought alone will keep Capricorns going. 
The Goat symbolizes Capricorns, and an apt mascot it is. Goats love to climb to the top of the mountain, where the air is clear and fresh. In much the same way, Capricorns want to get to the top of their chosen field so that they can reap the benefits of success; namely fame, prestige and money. Getting to the top isn't always a walk in the park, however, so it's likely that Goats will ruffle a few feathers along the way. These folks can indeed be domineering, even egotistical, on their route to the top. They'll tell you it's part of being a leader with bright new ideas (in keeping with the Cardinal Quality assigned to this Sign). 
Capricorns are industrious, efficient, organized and won't make a lot of waves. They are scrupulous with details and adopt a rather conventional posture in business and in life. These folks feel best playing it safe, since this is a fail-safe way to get to the top -- eventually. 
Thankfully, Capricorns are patient, too, and are happy to wait for their ship to come in. The flip side to this staid behavior is that Goats can become quite unforgiving of those who aren't as diligent or ambitious as they are. Capricorns need to remember that they do need allies along the way, ambitious or otherwise. In any case, once Capricorns receive the recognition and social status they so fervently crave, it's likely that all will be forgiven. 
Your Rising Sign is in Aquarius
If your Rising Sign is Aquarius, you may seem aloof and self-introspective, maybe a bit outlandish. Though you seem detached, you also give the impression that you care very deeply for humanity -- just not necessarily individual humans! You'll likely attract friends easily thanks to this Aquarian influence, but be wary of the more negative traits of the Water Bearer. Sometimes you can come off as rude or thoughtless -- as well as willfully eccentric. Despite these characteristics, you'll still be wildly popular, due in large part to what people see as the innovative Aquarian brain power.

Your Moon is in Cancer

You respond very much to the emotional tone and atmosphere around you, and can be dominated by your fluctuating and unpredictable moods. You often appear irrational to others because you cannot always explain the reason or source of your feelings. Anyone who lives with you must accept your ups and downs and appreciate your need for times of withdrawal.

You are also very sympathetic and understand the unspoken feelings and needs of others. You take slights and rebuffs very personally and though you may forgive a transgression by a friend or loved one, you never forget it.

Your Mercury is in Capricorn
Clear, objective, and realistic, you are unimpressed by exaggerated claims or promises. You insist upon being shown facts to back up any statement you hear, and your natural skepticism often borders on cynicism. You approach problems clearly and rationally and maintain your poise and objectivity even in the midst of critical situations. Anyone seeking your advice is certain to get an unemotional and unbiased assessment of their situation, and you therefore make a good arbitrator or judge. You are thorough, conscientious, and disciplined in your thinking, and have an aptitude for business, organization, and administration. You are also a good strategist, and will plan and patiently follow a realistic course which will lead to your eventual success. Serious-minded and studious, you enjoy quiet time alone for thinking or reading.

Your Venus is in Sagittarius 
The dance card is packed for those with their Venus in Sagittarius. Spotting one potential lover is not likely the case, for these folks are attracted to many. This is the kind of situation which can make life interesting, to say the least. Does this mean those with this placement will never settle down? Not necessarily - it just means the search for a mate will be a spirited one! What's essential in this search is turning up a partner with a similar quest for adventure and penchant for activity. The freedom to be is also ideal, and once committed, those with Venus in Sagittarius are loyal and honest in their relationships. Happy feet are likely to afflict those with Sagittarius in their House of Love, as they love to travel and have a wandering spirit. As well, any type of physical activity or body movement is zen to these folks. Yoga? Meditation? Bioenergetics? It's likely to work for these happy souls. When the Archer is shooting his bows into your Love shack, just hope that he brings along with him a kindred spirit who understands that mental and physical stimulation along with a lust for life will always hit the bull's-eye! 

Your Mars is in Capricorn
If your Mars is in Capricorn, you may have tremendous endurance and tenacity to accomplish what you put your mind to. You are focused and practical, bringing tremendous energy into a controlled and directed outlet. You work hard, and are a respectable, determined lover, worker, and friend. You are willing to put in the time it takes to build a relationship that is truly satisfying and mutually beneficial. Your lover will find you stable, thoughtful, and down to earth. Your potency attracts people who admire you and recognize you for your efforts and practical nature. Sensuality and a muted, underlying passionate nature make you an excellent catch for anyone who enjoys peace, stability, and a no nonsense approach to life! You offer stability to your relationships and are happiest when you and your partner are working toward a common goal.

Your Jupiter is in Leo
You can find luck through your own charisma and drama. Through your strong, enthusiastic personality, you can attract much success and attention -- sales or the theater are just two arenas where you could do well. Easy-going, you can let rejection roll off of you. You must, however, learn to temper your tendency toward exaggeration and pomposity if you want people to take you seriously.

Your Saturn is in Virgo
Your obsession with perfectionism and order can leave you feeling frustrated and in a rut. You have an almost compulsive attention to detail which may have been learnt from a parent or authority figure. Often times you discourage yourself and others from trying new things simply because they won't be done the way you think they should be. Your karmic path is to always feel trapped within the lines and yet afraid to color outside of them. Fear is the basic motivation behind this desire for order -- it is the only way you know of controlling your environment. If you are capable of overcoming this fear -- letting go of control -- you have a chance of developing an imaginative side where your practicality could become a valuable asset.

Your Chiron is in Taurus
If Chiron falls in Taurus in your chart, you bear a pain of neglect or that what you have is never enough. This Chironic placement makes a person who -- because of a wound of neglect (perhaps your parents were stingy with affection or even completely closed off from you) or actual physical hunger -- bears a mental or physical pain that weakens the spirit and body. At the heart of Taurus is a yearning for security and the pleasure of sensory stimulation: food, physical affection, bodily nourishment. Taurus loves to indulge, but with Chiron in Taurus, you're never quite full; as your stomach can feel empty, so too can your heart. Rather than wallowing in the haze of your hunger for what you lack, Chiron in Taurus encourages you to appreciate what you have. By cherishing gifts you already possess, you can share what you've learned from your pain with others. Give your time to causes dealing with a lack of resources: homelessness, hunger, neglected children, or for those wanting for affection or sensory or material comfort. 

Your Uranus is in Scorpio
When Uranus enters the already secretive Scorpio, it is a time of transformation. Those born with this placement will be consistently reinventing themselves, trying on new personas and personalities like so many wigs. You may compulsively search for change within yourself and the world around you. Issues surrounding sexuality might play an important part within your generation. There could be a backlash against the knowledge that, in this day and age, sex can kill. This could play out in extreme methods of sex and the dismantling of old taboos. During your time, you may find that topics such as sex and death stop being spoken of in whispers. This energy will also be harnessed into positive change. You may one day feel comfortable being exactly whom you choose to be. 

Your Neptune is in Sagittarius
You are part of a 14 year group of people that are extremely idealistic and farsighted in their dreams. Your age group is very liberal and expansive in outlook, and consequently churches become much more flexible and more eclectic in their approach during your life time. Religions that do not adapt to the broad-minded attitude of your age group simply are unable to attract very much interest and involvement from you.
A great deal of metaphysical musing and speculation is evident in your age group, and there is a very strong interest in all manner of psychic phenomena, UFO's, prophecy, etc. This interest will open many new doors and insights, but will also often lead to a great deal of fantasizing and speculation that is taken more seriously than it should be.

Your Pluto is in Libra
The focus of Libra is on relationships. Many babies are born when Pluto is in Libra as a result of their parents making efforts to improve and revitalize their relationships. These children grow up watching their parent's relationships either thrive or fail completely. This generation, however, is determined to make all of their partnerships work out. They watch what has worked for previous generations and incorporate it into their own lives, and they see what has failed in the past and try to make working changes. Some of those born while Pluto was in Libra might cast aside the idea of formal marriage in favor of more unconventional approaches to unity. Others, however, may decide that the free-form approach does not work and choose to rely on the more conservative elements that worked for marriage in earlier generations. 

Your Ceres is in Aquarius
Ceres-Aquarius retains the natural traits which makes the Aquarian Sun such a world-beater. You are not afraid to try new things, to innovate and discover, and that makes you a very powerful woman indeed. Instead of lazing around during your down time you'll want to nurture yourself and be out chasing your dreams, no matter how outrageous or unorthodox they may seem to others. You like to try new things and do things differently -- you may be the first to jump on new methods or technologies. Use your powerful brain and surging ambition in your free time and you'll be happily satisfied with your off-the-beaten-path style. Others see you as a natural leader, with the power and conviction to let you help others to realize their dreams. You support those you love and see merit in even their craziest ideas. Friends and associates will look to you for a shoring up, ensuring that you're in on the ground floor of new schemes. You don't intend to play the boss or team leader in new schemes, but may end up leading anyway as others fall behind your zeal and courage.

Your Juno is in Aquarius
The typical long-term relationship is not for you -- you won't be satisfied with contentment or with comfortable bickering. Your partnership is likely to be different than the norm. Perhaps you will negotiate for more time to follow your daring schemes, or you may be involved in long-distance relationships or in otherwise unusual partnerships. Whatever you work out you will negotiate with your usual charm and desire for independence. Too much togetherness is your bane; you need time on your own to carry out your plans and desires. You are willing to try anything once, which can bring both exciting and unusual experiences and downfalls when you let your heart rule your head. Domesticity is not for you either, and you may find that you never settle down into a long-term partnership. It's not that you can't or that no one wants you; instead, it may be you who rejects comfort for excitement and Juno-Aquarians who make this choice will get love and affection from friends and family instead.

Your Pallas is in Capricorn
Leading just comes naturally to you and you excel at showing others what needs to be done and setting them on the proper path. You're a natural authority, and will find yourself taking over any group which lets you do it! Others look to you as an authority, even those who are older and more experienced than you, because your natural confidence shows through whatever you do. Pallas-Capricorn is a superb fighter to have on any team -- you rally to causes in which you believe and see them through to the end. You're the first into battle and the last to leave the battlefield. The vague ideas and plans which others have are crystallized under your lead -- you excel at turning plans into reality with your firm practicality. You are gifted with drive, determination and plenty of ambition, both in your career and personal life. Others may occasionally see your authority as intrusive, but most will be more than willing to let you take charge as is your natural inclination.

Your Vesta is in Aquarius
You are happiest when you're devoted to a cause in which you idealistically believe in, especially one in which you feel you're leading others down a path to a better future. Vesta-Aquarius is a superb leader, but your talents are better suited to leading a group rather than the one-on-one service perhaps others would prefer. Your boundless energy is well-used to further a cause in which you believe, particularly a humanitarian or political movement. You will work tirelessly for your ideals and you care deeply about advancing rights and freedom for yourself and for others. Someone needs a creative thinker? That's you all over. Your downfall is a tendency to selfishness -- you may seem sometimes to care more about the welfare of the masses than those close to you, even though your friendships are vital to you. Vesta-Aquarians may also have a great need to define and focus aspirations rather than just striking out at full power. This strategy helps to focus your commitment, and the support you receive from your many friends will complete the deed. In the bedroom you will enjoy anything which is unusual and you'll try anything at least once.

Leo Descendant

If Leo lies on your Descendant, you're hunting for a mate who is as gregarious and sociable as you, but who possesses the sort of resolute confidence and emotional expressiveness that you sometimes feel you lack. Since you have Aquarius Rising -- a Sign associated with aloof intellectuality and humanitarian interests -- you need a mate who will counter your self-deprecating pride with their own brand of pride -- of a more effervescent, positive variety. You hold your own in the spotlight, assured and well-spoken. When the attention turns to your love life, though, to sharing your most intimate emotions with another person, you run and hide, fearful of being pinned down or caged; and yet you instinctually seek out romantic partners who are steadfast and loyal and who will worship you and spoil you with unconditional support and affection.
